$ System.Management.Automation.PSReference (class)

`System.Management.Automation.PSReference` defines a type for a reference object that are used when passing
→  Windows/PowerShell/language/object[objects] *by reference*.

`PSReference` is used to for two (both?) kinds of references:
    • reference to a value: `_value` stores the value being referenced.
    • reference to a → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable: `_value` stores a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/PSVariable[`PSVariable`] instance for the variable to be referenced.
